<item>
            <title>[PIG-2920] e2e tests override PERL5LIB environment variable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2920</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am not sure why but e2e tests set PERL5LIB like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;env key=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;PERL5LIB&quot;&lt;/span&gt; value=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;./libexec&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This overrides any env variable, so there is no way to use custom Perl installations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch just removes the line, thus we will rely on the user to configure PERL5LIB appropriately.&lt;br/&gt;
With this modification I am able to use my custom Perl installation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
